records.u_deployment_instructions:
Update Set: 
STRY0471750-Sonam-EnableCABWorkbenchPlugin (Application: Global)
STRY0471750-Sonam-EnableCABWorkbenchPlugin (Application: Change Management - CAB Workbench)
records.acceptance_criteria:
Once CAB Workbench plugin is enabled OOB usecases listed below should be tested & validated:
•	Create a CAB definition
CAB Definitions are similar to a recurring meeting invitation. When you define a CAB definition, it determines the attributes that are associated with all CAB Meetings generated from that definition.
•	Create a single CAB meeting occurrence
Depending on your requirements, you can create an individual CAB meeting occurrence.
•	Modify CAB meeting details
You can modify the agenda items for a specific CAB meeting.
•	Send CAB meeting request to attendees
You can send CAB meeting invites to attendees for each CAB meeting.

- Allow Delete of CAB Definitions/CAB Meetings to sn_change_cab.cab_manager Role users (Modify ACLs)
- Add Role sn_change_cab.cab_manager role to All CAB meetings and My Cab Meetings module
records.description:
Enable CAB workbench plugin (com.snc.change_management.cab): Change Management - CAB Workbench


The Change Advisory Board (CAB) workbench enables a CAB manager to schedule, plan, and manage CAB meetings.
CAB meetings are typically intended to review and authorize change requests and review recently implemented changes. A standard agenda with the relevant change request details enables the CAB members to conduct risk and impact analysis prior to the CAB meeting.
The CAB workbench assists you in managing CAB meetings in the following ways:
•	Define a schedule for CAB meetings: Schedule a recurring series of CAB meetings for CAB members to assess the impact and risk or change requests prior to the meetings.
•	Define CAB meeting attendees: Define members who attend this CAB meeting series for each occurrence. For example, define the CAB board members or any delegates who can substitute if the CAB manager cannot attend.
•	Define CAB meeting agenda: Define filter criteria that determines which change requests are included in any occurrence of a CAB Meeting. If a change request is included in an agenda, the change requester is notified of the CAB meeting in which their change request is discussed. The change requester can then present the reasons for the proposed change and explain the intended outcomes and potential risks of the change to the CAB.
•	View change calendar: Schedule changes by displaying existing planned changes in a change calendar in daily, weekly, and monthly view. The calendar view also displays maintenance windows and blackout schedules, if any.
•	Approve or reject a change request: Approve or reject a change request based on the decision taken in the CAB meeting.
•	View and record meeting notes: Record meeting notes from a specific CAB meeting and share these notes with other meeting attendees.
records.u_development_changes:
Plugin has been activated and verified.

Following customizations have been incorporated:

  • Allow Delete of CAB Definitions/CAB Meetings to sn_change_cab.cab_manager Role users (Modify ACLs)
  • Add Role sn_change_cab.cab_manager role to All CAB meetings and My Cab Meetings module
  • All the tabs have been aligned with the change request form fields (cab-workbench view)
  • Two fields are missing from Change tab (Risk value, Peer Reviewer) [Added these two fields]
  • Planning fields have scroll, but are still far too short to display content to where we could easily review Changes. Description field on Change also needs this fix with scroll and height. [Increased the height and added scrollbar wherever required]
  • Added time zone conversion for “Change Requests starting after/before” Fields.
  • CAB Workbench module visible to only itil, non-itil user.

 

Update set: Link(Global) , Link(Change Management - CAB Workbench)

records.short_description: SAM (Software Asset Management) : Use Case SCCM Integration/Software Usage.
records.task: SAM (Software Asset Management) : Use Case SCCM Integration/Software Usage.​STRY0605928
records.description:
Description: SCCM Integration/Software Usage.

The Microsoft System Center Configuration Manager (SCCM) 2012 integration is a one direction import of SCCM data into the ServiceNow Configuration Management Database (CMDB). Scheduled imports bring relevant data from SCCM tables into the CMDB through the SQL database and map them to the ServiceNow instance.

For this need to enable the Plugin "Integration - Microsoft SCCM 2012 v2 "on Jakarta and this integration will help in Usage Metering. The operations team will be able to identify the Software Entitlements that are not being used and will be able to set up reclamation rules based on that.

There won't be much Development effort needed but we need to Perform Regression testing of the Product to verify it working as expected and meeting the Business Requirements.

Scenarios that need to be tested here are:

Create new record with mandatory fields and records should be successfully submitted.

Select all mandatory fields and Click on Submit.
